title: SAF regular serviceman dies after losing consciousness in Pasir Laba Camp
text: Photo of Pasir Laba Camp: Google Street More A Singapore Armed Forces (SAF) regular serviceman died after losing consciousness in Pasir Laba Camp on Friday morning. Second Warrant Officer (2WO) Sim Poh Wah, 44, lost consciousness at 7.53am, and resuscitative efforts were administered on him immediately, the Ministry of Defence (Mindef) said in a media release. 2WO Sim was evacuated to the medical centre in the camp and later to Ng Teng Fong General Hospital via an SAF ambulance. An SAF medical officer and medics continued to resuscitate him along the way. The ambulance arrived at the hospital at 8.45am. 2WO Sim was pronounced dead at 9am. Mindef and the SAF extend their deepest condolences to the family of 2WO Sim. The SAF is helping the family in their time of grief. Reblog
